Description: Implementation of the Change Detection by Multispectral Trends (CDMT) algorithm for mapping inter-annual changes in Landsat time series.
    CDMT employs the High-dimensional Trend Segmentation (HiTS) procedure proposed by Maeng (2019) to detect changepoints at the pixel level.
    Landsat time series can be either univariate or multivariate.        
